Please read Putin's response:  Posted online on Dec 14, 2017, Putin On Washington Asking For Russian Help: Associated Press journalist Kate de Pure question to Vladimir Putin, “the US wants Russia to persuade NK to curtail it’s missile program. Does Russia support stricter sanctions against NK. Do you think cooperation with NK could warm up relations with the US, with the US under Mr. Trump?.
PUTIN says:
You’re some curious folks I’ll give you that. Have you paid attention to your congress  and senators.(Joke-dresscode). They seem to be smart people. They’ve placed us on par with North Korea and Iran. And at the same time, they’re pushing Trump to persuade us to cooperate with the nuclear crises in NK and Iran. You OK there? It seems plain weird to me. It’s beyond common sense. But our policy unlike the policy of some other countries always retains it’s initial course. We’re trying to cooperation with everybody on acutest issues of the international security. We try not to get offended, we hold the grudge when some country makes a questionable decision. But our position on NK is well known. We don’t acknowledge the nuclear status of NK. We consider everything that’s happening there to be COUNTER PRODUCTIVE. I’d like to remind you In 2005, North Korea signed an agreement on stopping its nuclear program.  North Korea took certain responsibilities. Everyone gladly signed these agreements. And several months later, it occurred to the US that these agreements weren’t enough. They instantly seized the account of the NK banks and said NK had to do something more. Beyond the signed agreements NK said “screw this”, terminate the agreements and turned to developing Nuclear Weapons, WHY DID you do this? Did you think it wasn’t enough? Why did you sign the initial agreements then? You provoked NK to terminate them. And then even worse: Libya, Iraq.  I’ve addressed the issue multiple times. NK sees no way to survive other than by developing the weapons of mass destruction and missiles. They’ve recently developed a missile that could reach the US territory. From the look of it. The situation is awful. We think that both sides need to stop provoking each other. Our American partners have said: “all right, we’ll stop the drills", Nope. Here they go conducting another one. And NK launched another missile. This spiral must be finished. The situation is extremely dangerous. We’ve discussed it with our US partners. If we assume the US would deliver strikes the conventional ones the precise non nuclear strikes where would it hit?  Does CIA or DIA know exactly what targets to strike? With one shot. Of course no, NK is a closed state. You might know something but not everything. And NK is one launch away from a global cataclysm. A cataclysm. Yes, the US has resorted to nuclear weapons against Japan, Without a reasonable basis, if you ask me. But now there’s absolutely no need. One must be extremely careful. Today, Mr. Tillerson said that the US is ready for a direct contact. That’s great news. It means that the US authority and the State Department are beginning to realize what’s going on in the world. I hope together with the DIA and the Pentagon they’ll apply common sense and act accordingly. In that case we’ll gladly cooperate with the US on all such issues including NK.
